==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lætere Sunday
<hw>L⟦ae⟧*te"re Sun"day</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The fourth
Sunday of Lent; -- so named from the Latin word <xex>L⟦ae⟧tare</xex>
(rejoice), the first word in the antiphone of the introit sung that day
in the Roman Catholic service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laevigate</ent>⟦br⟧
